gomodel:SYNGO_1359  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig9AB shows EFA6C localization in dendrites of Purkinje cells and spines by light microscopy, Fig9D shows postsynaptic localization by immuno-EM, which is verified by subcellular fractionation where EFA6C shows enrichment in the PSD95 fraction (Fig8B).\n\n24/10/2017 Pim\n- The authors mention \"showing strong immunoreactivity in the dendritic spines (sp) having the post-synaptic density (arrows)\". The immuno-EM picture is rather vague but staining seems to be more widespread than the PSD itself.. Experimental description: Figure legends \"adult mouse cerebellum \"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5259-4945" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-02" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1359" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

